{
  "text": "Instead, the findings here suggest that most of the DNA hypomethylation changes examined in this study were highly C content reduction changes in multiple metastatic deposits from different subjects. CpG island hypermethylation data, collected by real-time methylation-specific PCR (RT-MSP ), were obtained from a previous study [CITATION_1] and are color-scaled with red representing complete methylation of >99% (hypermethylation) of input alleles and white representing no methylation. * in the hypermethylation data indicates that there was a low but detectable level of hypermethylation. DNA hypomethylation data at gene-specific CpG islands and at LINE1 promoters, as determined in this study on the same samples and cases as the previous study examining CpG island hypermethylation changes, were color-scaled with white representing >99% of all input alleles being methylated and dark blue representing no methylation (hypomethylation). 5me C content was color scaled with white representing a 5me C content of >0.04 (corresponding to the levels seen in normal WBCs) and dark blue representing no 5me C content. On average, hypomethylation changes were more variable across sites within the same subject compared with the CpG island hypermethylation changes (for gene-specific CpG islands, P V 10 \u00c010 ; for LINE1 promoter hypomethylation, P < 10 \u00c03 ; for 5me C content, P < 10",
